p: Data extracted from the National HIV Registry for this analysis were year and age at diagnosis, sex, country of birth (routinely collected from 2002), mode of exposure to HIV (males who have sex with males (MSM); MSM with dual risk of injecting drug use (IDU); heterosexual sex; and other/undetermined exposure, including mother-to-child transmission, direct blood/tissue exposure, and iatrogenic exposure, likely place of acquisition (Australia or overseas) and year of arrival in Australia.
